OVERVIEW:
Player gameplay APIs for SectorWars 2102. Covers in-game Player state, ship pointer, sector location, lazy turn regeneration, ARIA-driven first-login onboarding, and the Galactic Citizen / Region Owner lifecycle hooks (emergency relocation, owner relocation, planet-safe and station prepay). Player and First Login are surfaced as two distinct routers.

FACTS:
* Base URLs: /api/v1/player, /api/v1/players, /api/v1/first-login
* Auth: JWT Bearer (issued by /api/v1/auth/*); same JWT used for WebSocket upgrade
* sector_id is INTEGER (matches Sector.sector_id), not UUID; player/ship/region IDs are UUID
* Turns: continuous lazy regeneration (target spec) — base rate 1000/86400 t/s, scaled by Player.aria_bonus_multiplier (1.0×–1.5×), capped at Player.max_turns (1000 + rank bonus)
* Currently shipping: once-per-UTC-day reset via ranking_service.refresh_daily_turns; columns last_turn_regeneration / max_turns are design-only pending Alembic migration
* First login: stateful AI dialogue with Callisto Colony shipyard guard; 6 personality archetypes; 5-exchange hard cap per session; escape pod is the always-safe fallback
* Initial player spawn: Sector 1 of Terran Space (300-sector fixed starter region)
* Realtime: turn_pool_updated unicast event after successful regen (target taxonomy)

TERMINOLOGY:
* Player: in-game state row (1:1 with User), separate from auth account
* Turn: lazy-regenerating action currency, integer
* Sector: integer-keyed location row; planets/stations/ships hang off it
* Ship: registered hull; Player.current_ship_id points to the active one
* First Login: AI-driven onboarding that creates the Player row + starter Ship + initial credits
* Nickname: optional in-game callsign captured at first-login (3–20 chars, unique, profanity/impersonation-filtered); falls back to User.username when null
* Galactic Citizen: $5/mo subscription tier; sets Player.is_galactic_citizen = true and unlocks cross-region warp from the Nexus

